Polythiophene is a conducting polymer with applications for manufacturing sensors, supercapacitors, batteries, and anti-corrosion of metals. This is due to conducting polymers’ unique electrical, chemical, magnetic, thermal, and high electron mobility properties. The simplicity of polythiophene’s fabrication methods, such as chemical-oxidative, solid state, metal-catalyzed coupling reaction, acid-catalyzed, and electro-polymerization, have been considerably reported [25]. However, it was reported by Lu et al. [25] that some of the methods mentioned earlier are responsible for the rigid backbone and π\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
